article_title: Citizens Financial's Debut Quiets Some Skeptics
article_text:
Citizens Financial Group Inc. scored in its return to the U.S. stock market Wednesday, rising 7.4% to cap off the regional lender's first day as a publicly traded company in 26 years.

The shares' gains came a day after the Providence, R.I., firm concluded a 10-day roadshow that saw active debate over the price being asked for the shares. Executives led by Chief Executive Bruce Van Saun sought to persuade skeptical investors to buy the shares, culminating in an initial-public-offering pricing that fell short of...
